nd the string followed across the parapet, and the revolver came next—all splash into the water. Only I can’t remember why it was necessary.”

“Smooth water, in brief; and a dead man left on the bridge. What a good thing coffee is! I had a splitting headache; now it’s much better. So that’s clear to you, more or less—I mean the way it all has to happen.”

I sipped the fiery coffee and meditated the while. Odd, she had no imagination whatever. In a couple of days life changes—to